#import "../../../shared/environments.typ": *

#hypothesis(title: [Circadian Misallocation of Energy Budget])[
The selective energy dysfunction hypothesis (Chapter @sec:selective-dysfunction, lines 628–645) proposes that suprachiasmatic nucleus (SCN) dysfunction impairs circadian allocation of the CNS energy budget, explaining energy availability mismatches across the day.

*Certainty: 0.35* (mechanistically plausible; circadian disruption documented in ME/CFS @cambras2018circadian @castromarrero2021melatonin; direct evidence for SCN-specific energy allocation dysfunction lacking)
]
